title: @OspreyWGolf in 5th After 36 holes of Play at Pinehurst Challenge
text: @OspreyWGolf in 5th After 36 holes of Play at Pinehurst Challenge North Florida Athletics Day 1 Results (pdf) PINEHURST, N.C. -- The North Florida women's golf team sits in fifth-place at 577 after posting two of the best rounds in program history on the opening day of play Monday in the Pinehurst Challenge at Pinehurst No.1 Course (par 72 / 5,949 yards) of Pinehurst Country Club.UNF started the 36-hole day with a solid round of 290, the fourth best round in program history, before closing the day with a one-under par 287, the second best round in program history. Senior led the way for the Ospreys firing a morning round of 4-under 68, the lowest round in program history, followed by an even-par 72 to rank seventh with a total of 140.Junior
